<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - PriceScope</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        main {
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .policy-box {
            background: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            max-width: 90%;
            margin: auto;
            text-align: left;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #142850;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-weight: bold;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #00aaff;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
        }

        p,
        ul {
            color: #333;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }
    </style>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

</head>

<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>
      
    <main>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <section class="policy-box">
            <p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how PriceScope collects, uses, and protects
                your personal data.</p>

            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>We collect the following types of information when you use our platform:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal Information: Name, email address, and account details.</li>
                <li>Usage Data: Browsing history, search queries, and interactions with our website.</li>
                <li>Cookies and Tracking: Data collected through cookies to enhance user experience.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use your data for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Providing and improving our services.</li>
                <li>Personalizing your experience and recommendations.</li>
                <li>Sending updates, newsletters, and promotional offers (if subscribed).</li>
                <li>Ensuring security and preventing fraudulent activities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>3. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
            <p>We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share it with trusted third parties such as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Service providers assisting in website operation.</li>
                <li>Legal authorities when required by law.</li>
                <li>Third-party advertisers (only anonymized data).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
            <p>We use cookies to enhance your experience. You can manage cookie preferences in your browser settings.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement security measures to protect your data but cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access, modify, or delete your personal data. Contact us for any data-related
                requests.</p>

            <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on our website.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@pricescope.com.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
          const toggle = document.querySelector(".dropdown-toggle");
          const dropdown = document.querySelector(".dropdown");
      
          if (toggle && dropdown) {
            toggle.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
              e.stopPropagation();
              dropdown.classList.toggle("active");
            });
      
            document.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
              if (!dropdown.contains(e.target)) {
                dropdown.classList.remove("active");
              }
            });
          }
        });
      </script>
      
</body>

</html>